        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_fag" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fag</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fagæ</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>достаточно</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>enough</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вдоволь</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>plenty</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>достаточный</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>sufficient</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>mæ fag, dæ fag</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>достаточный для меня, для тебя</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>enough for me and for you</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>æppætæj dær fag</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>всего вдоволь</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>plenty of everything</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>53</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>wæ xwærd wæ fagæ ku adtæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ведь еды у вас было вдоволь</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>because you had plenty of food</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>30</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kæd kæræʒījy fag næ rævdydtam?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>разве мы недостаточно ласкали друг друга?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>didn't we caress each other enough?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>(fīw) afæʒ-vag ū rast</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>(сала) хватит как раз на год</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>lard is enough just for a year</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>92</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>æz mæxwædæg oj fagæ isoʒænæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>меня самой достаточно для него (т. е. „я сама с ним справлюсь“)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I am enough for him (that is, "I can handle him myself")</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_LQ"/><biblScope>III
                            39</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>īs, fælloj sæm fag wydī</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>имущества, богатства было у них вдоволь</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they had plenty of property and wealth</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>75</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>īw ærḱʼī ʒy bajsærston (fīwæj), īnnæjy fag nal yssī</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>один %særḱʼi%s я смазал (жиром), на другой уже не хватило</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I greased one %særḱʼi%s, but there wan't enough fat for the other</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>119</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">G. %sMorgenstierne%s (<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII 267</biblScope></bibl>)
                    сопоставляет с <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pāka-</w>
                        <gloss><q>зрелость</q></gloss></mentioned>. Однако основное значение
                    последнего слова — ‘варка’, ‘кипячение’ — плохо согласуется с %ifag%i. Ближе
                    семантически стоит <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>pāk</w>
                        <gloss><q>omnis</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>totus</q></gloss></mentioned> (наряду с <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>pāk</w>
                        <gloss><q>чистый</q></gloss></mentioned>). Не исключена возможность
                    образования из *ap-āka- от ap- ‘достигать’. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Шегрен"/><biblScope>68</biblScope></bibl>: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ar"><lang/>
                        <w>faqat</w>
                        <gloss><q>только</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">G. %sMorgenstierne%s (<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII 267</biblScope></bibl>)
                    relates it to <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pāka-</w>
                        <gloss><q>maturity</q></gloss></mentioned>. However, the main meaning of the
                    latter word — ‘cooking’, ‘boiling’ — does not agree well with %ifag%i. The word
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>pāk</w>
                        <gloss><q>omnis</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>totus</q></gloss></mentioned> (alongside with <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>pāk</w>
                        <gloss><q>clean</q></gloss></mentioned>) is more close to it from semantic
                    point of view. It is also possible that it was derived from *ap-āka- (from ap-
                    ‘reach’). — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Шегрен"
                            /><biblScope>68</biblScope></bibl>: <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/>
                        <w>faqat</w>
                        <gloss><q>only</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
            </entry>
